reviews.review_text: Pharmacy manager goes beyond to provide exceptional service. Phone in automated refill service is great. Some of the pharmacy technicians could use some customer service retraining or learn to experience some empathy. Try not to go during peak business hours, lines ups will be long. The wait for prescriptions will be approximately 45 mins - 1 hour. Do your grocery shopping while you wait.

April update: the staff are great. I see them hustle every time I get medication filled. They are understaffed and overworked but do their best to help. Any issues I ve had in the past are out of their control.
Manager is handsome and helpful. Staff are kind.

I always get my medication here and I never had any problems. Often times the medication is ready later than stated, but they do seem very busy all the time. I feel like everyone is working hard, they may just be a bit understaffed, hence the delays.
Very nice staff, its my go to for medication needs.  Doris is the best !
This is a good supper store One of the better ones The staff are good And they always have what you are looking for
Staff is always helpful
Love it, very convenient
Nice
Ive only had great experiences with this place... Except one time they couldnt figure out how to charge my insurance place in person (we figured it out over the phone later that day)
Friendly pharmacist and alot quicker then most pharmacys

I see other peoples reviews here saying its not a great place- but I would disagree. The wait time when I come in on a friday and saturday has not been bad at all, and the staff are friendly and knowledgeable. I mean, its a simple clinic inside a superstore, you already dont want to be there when youre in there, but its not as bad as everyone has been saying, in my experience anyway
They always get it right and theyre a compounding pharmacy. However, their waits are very long.
Wonderful people and great service
Good price
Clinic and pharmacy pharmacy
They sell all kinds of medicines

Located inside the Real Canadian Super Store inset off of Marine Dr near Main Str in South Vancouver. There can be a bit of a wait to fill your prescription. But the staff is friendly & knowledgeable. And the  pharmacy is  well stocked bright and clean. Flu shot are also available here. The best part is you can do all your grocery shopping here while they fill the prescription. And lots of free parking .
Customer service is poor . If you call them to ask for particular medicine they always say we dont have this med. .
Good prices...pharmacists are great...the assistants are hit and miss
So so pharmacy.
Good drug store

Dropped off my prescription at 5pm today and was told that it will be ready in 1 hour, so I leave and come back at 6:30pm because I know their estimate is never right. I go up to the counter to pick up my medication and they tell me to wait on the side for 5 minutes and pointed towards the medication information corner. I wait in the medication information corner for about 40 minutes while they process 10 other people who received and paid for medications. The person who initially told me to wait for 5 minutes left to go for her break and did not tell anyone about my prescription. I went to line up again for the prescription pickup line and they just took it from the counter and gave it to me. I dont understand why the person who went for their break did not just process my prescription when it was already ready and on the counter.

I dont want to be rude and I dont usually like to leave negative reviews but this place is very... Challenging, Ill say. I havent had much of a problem at the counter or with wait times, but the first few times I filled a prescription they kept forgetting or failing to bill my extended benefits. Annoying but not awful. My biggest challenge is refills. The phone number currently printed on the bottles is incorrect. The phone number listed on Google is also wrong. Even the automated system you get when you call Superstore sends you to the wrong number. I had to get someone at the customer service desk to tell me the number, hang up, and redial it directly. I picked this pharmacy because I recently moved nearby and I usually get my groceries at Superstore, so this seemed like an easy decision. How could it be less convenient than driving 25 minutes across town to my old pharmacy near my old apartment? Superstore accepted my challenge and exceeded my expectations.

Generally poor service.  Prescription isnt always ready when automated telephone refill time says it will.  Have refilled a prescription 3 months in a row and every time they didnt have enough stock to fill it - hello - you have a customer with refills on the prescription you should know that they are coming back to refill in a month and get some stock in!!  Also shortened the hours on stat holidays without posting it on the website so I went without meds another time.  I have switched to another pharmacy.
I tried to drop off prescribed mouth wash which I got from them before. The lady saw the paper and gave me a very rude attitude telling me they dont carry it.
Dont sell high quality product

Save yourself some stress by going to a different pharmacy! I should have checked the google reviews before wasting my time. ALL the pharmacy staff in this location is a joke. No regard for privacy, they look like they don t know what they re doing, doesn t communicate properly and looks like they don t want to be there to do a proper job! What a shame, such unprofessional team.

Very very disappointed with staff. I went to pharmacy today around 11:30am and there was long line ups and i understand they were busy. However, the female pharmacist she looks very tired with no smile at all and she looks like she doesnt care at all. Also, there was another asian female staff at pick up prescription area and she was super rude. I didnt understand what she told me was and i asked same question twice and suddenly both of staff(female pharmacist and pick up area staff) they were laughing in front of me which is ridiculous and very rude. This pharmacy needs to re-train your staff there, all the staff there was super rude and they need to learn how to greet customer and also need to learn how to smile at customer. I will never visit this pharmacy never again!! very unprofessional
Stay away! Such Unprofessionals are working there. 1, super long wait time. 2, poor communication 3, Big mistake, I found someones durg in my receipt bag. Please find a better pharmacy and stay safe.

Its my first time to go this pharmacy and it was terrible.  When I drop my prescription, Darison helped me but she was very rude and disrespect the customer. She think queen of the pharmacy or something. And she told me will be ready after 35min then when I pick up my staff they are not ready. I was waiting extra 1 hour..... Can you please hire good manger here?

I have not felt inclined to leave a google review until now because of how BAD my experience was today. I called them before going there, and they told me they had enough stock to give me two refills and that it would be 40 minutes. In previous times I have gone, they have taken longer than they said they would, so this time I came after 50 minutes instead of 40 to give them more time. When I arrived they made me wait ANOTHER 20 MINUTES! I ended up waiting DOUBLE the time they estimated. When they finally called me to the counter they informed me that they were 6 pills short and that I would need to come back in THREE DAYS to get them! A few of the staff members are rude as well. Especially a short-haired blonde woman who might be a supervisor, Im not sure. She seems to have no empathy whatsoever.

Very rude and indifferent Pharmacy staff. I went in to pick up an RX, which I dropped off several days prior. They had to order the medication and told me it would be available in 2 days. To be sure, I went to pick it up 5 days later. The rude staff member then told me  oh we  didnt order it, check back later. Excuse me but I do have a life outside of constantly running in and out of a  pharmacy to pick up my now week  old RX! It would have nice if she offered an apology for my inconvenience, or asked if Id be interested in delivery to save me a 3rd trip into the store, but the only sound that came out of her mouth was next, clearly indicating that she couldnt care less about the customers she is paid to serve, and hated her job.

Went to get prescription eye drops for my eye that was swelling a little bit. I asked the lady receptionist how much it will cost approximately and the lady couldnt answer because she cant remember the price off the top of her head and brushed it off. Alright, she was a little rude, but okay. 30+ minutes later I came back to pick it up. I was supposed to receive 5ml of the solution, but was given 10ml. I did research after that to find out that the company manufacturing the solution either stopped or did not manufacture the 5ml solution. I understand that its not the pharmacys fault, but I just find it unfair to be charged for a higher dosage than what I was anticipating and prescribed and not be told about it when picking it up. Only to find out when getting home.

Every time I have been to this pharmacy the wait times have been unbelievable. I understand there are lots of orders to fill but if they know they are never going to fill the prescription in a said amount of time so why do they continue to tell everyone an unrealistic wait time. 35 minutes is alot of time to wait in the first place but when almost every persons wait time is double that.....STOP TELLING PEOPLE YOULL BE DONE IN 35 MINUTES!!!! If you would just tell people come back in an hour, then maybe youd have enough time to do the orders and your reviews wouldnt be so terrible.

Prices are good but the service is terrible. They were supposed to renew my prescription one month ago and didnt follow up. It is the pharmacys responsibility to follow-up and ensure the fax gets to the Dr. They never followed up. Im out of my prescription and they are not doing a very good job of following up now. What do I do without my prescription? Go blind?!?! I need my eye drops!!!! They told me to relax. Condescending and rude is what that is.

The service is really bad and one of their staff is super rude, unbelievable. I dont know her name, but she is a girl with short hair and usually stand in the drop off prescription area. The story is I got the prescription from the doctor, and my insurance benefit can cover 100% my bill with the prescription. When I showed my insurance benefit card, she was impatient and said you should give me earlier. Why she didnt ask me earlier? That is okay, after she said this medicine cant be covered by my insurance. I said it is impossible because my insurance cover 100% medicine with prescription. She became very impatient and rude, and said you should check your insurance first, then come. I was really annoyed why I should check first? If I check, how I can know which prescription that doctor will provide me? After she asked me to go to another counter to pay the money in full, she left without any words. It is very horrible service and I feel really uncomfortable. I dont mind If I cant get covered by insurance, but she should treat customer with basic respect, not challenge and rude all the time. I still remember last time I was there and drop off my prescription, and asked her some questions, and she was very impatient as well.  I wont go to this pharmacy anymore, never!!!

I would have arrived a few minutes before their 8pm closing to get a flu shot, but I was turned away on the phone and told to return tomorrow. I arrived anyway and parked with 4m before closing. I thought the flu shot was at the upstairs medical clinic so I climbed those stairs. After seeing those doors closed, I realized it must be at the inside store pharmacy. When I reached the pharmacy, it was still before 8pm, but it looked like it was closed already. I called my brother to check other pharmacies still open and was told of a competitor nearby thats open till 12am. So Im going there now to get my flu shot instead.

WORST PHARMACY - I dont think I have ever had a good experience here and that is in all honesty. Every single time I come here (and I dont know why I keep coming back, this pharmacy messes up my prescriptions, my orders, everything). Today my doctor called in my prescription at 3PM and they said they had no record of it. Every time I order something, they never have it on time or they never call me. They are rude, they are not helpful and they have very poor customer service.

Last summer,  I asked the pharmacy to order for me an unavailable prescription drug and one of the staff said it should be ready in 5 days.  After five days I went back it wasnt there yet.  So another order was placed according to the staff.  A week later I came back and it still wasnt there.  Turned out nobody from the staff was placing the order.  Complained this to the management, that was all thats needed for the pharmacy staff to go into action of finally ordering the meds.  Some of the drugstore staff have very mean attitudes, though some are okay.  Dont go there to buy prescription, buy them somewhere else.

I am not racist but I called today and this indian lady who answered my call was in a hurry and she answered me we dont have that ok? I told her I am a customer there and i bought PTU and she said we have on hand and so i said I need my meds, she cannot find my name 3x I spelled it for her,  i told her i have a presc number and she checked and later she said they dont have that much amount even half of the month ok???!!! so she wanted to hang up the phone, so i said whats the rush? I am ordering my meds, she kept talking over me and I was telling her to order for me and Ill pick it up tomorrow, I dont know if she understood, but this is so rediculous if I dont have my meds tomorrow, I am going to flip. Shes so rude ever. I dont care if they are busy, they should hire more staffs, In fact I am paying my meds.

Absolutely worst pharmacy. Only go as nessecary..  if you have absolutely any other options take them. You will wait forever for even the most important medication. Even after they know the doctor wants it refilled they fought me . I find them to actually be abusive and the worst

Honestly, I don t know why I came back here again. The service never improves. It s slow, the staff is not friendly, and I just get so frustrated. The placement is convenient, but I d rather just drive further to Shopper s.

I waited 1 hour to get my eye drops. 1 HOUR!!!! Thats insane Ive never been to a slower pharmacy in my life, and they werent busy. I cant imagine how long it will take if they were busy. Im sorry but I dont recommend this place to anyone.
Called ahead so my prescription would be ready when I got there.  They said it would take an hour.  I came by 3.5 hours later but it wasnt ready yet :/
Another disappointment with this place the pharmacy is unprofessional workers they dont have the knowledge about medicine.  Whos the person who run this place
This place is brutal. Waiting in 3 different line ups. Pay here, wait here, pay again, wait for counseling.  30+ minutes to get prescriptions I called in days ago.
Made a special trip to order a refill.  Was told they had no record of my prescription and made no effort to double check.  According to the bottle I found at home, I have 3 refills.

This pharmacy is the absolute worst. The front desk staff are vapid rude and have zero bedside manner. They inform you that you will be waiting 20-40 minutes and it s oten double that time. If I could give it zero stars I would.

We ve been getting our medication every 4 weeks from Richmond s Superstore many years. Just told they changed policy we can only get our prescriptions 2 weeks at a time. Now we have to pay double the fees and have to make extra trip monthly. We are looking for another provider.

Very inefficient. Wastes your time. Told me the prescription will be ready in 45 minutes. Came back 5 hours later, still wasnt ready and told me itll be another 15minutes. Did my grocery shopping and 30minutes later it was still not ready.
Service here is one of the most unprofessional i ve experienced. Please go somewhere else where they will take care of your prescription with more care.
Terrible people work here, AVOID AT ALL COSTS! How are you going to ask me if im okay to wait TWO HOURS to fill an inhaler prescription when im clearly having an asthma attack right at the counter?
Literally took an hour to prescribe over-the-counter eyedrops. The pharmacist didnt even explain and just made me pay. Ill never be there again.
The WORST experience ever!! Extremely bad service from their staffs!! Two out of three staffs were rude, not helpful at all & absolutely not sure what they were doing!!
Wish I saw the reviews here before going. There are better pharmacies that value your time.

loooooooooooooooooooooong lines, usually only 2 cashiers working to attend a massive crowd, how bout maybe having 2 more cashiers, its a very busy store/location... also is usually dirty everywhere....
Very long wait No proper management
People work here are so rude and unprofessional.
Bad service long waits
Not what you think.
Terrible Service
slow slow slow slow slow slow slow slow
